      <projectDescription>
        Graphics for Understanding Mathematical Programming in Python (GrUMPy)
        is a Python library for visualizing various aspects of mathematical programming,
        including visualizations of the branch-and process, branch-and-bound trees,
        polyhedra, cutting plane methods, etc. The goal is clarity in implementation rather
        than efficiency. Most methods have an accompanying visualization and are
        thus appropriate for use in the classroom.
      </projectDescription>

      <projectShortDescription>
        A Python library for visualizing algorithms for solving mathematical
        optimization problems. 
      </projectShortDescription>

